<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-60-0928 </DOCNO><TEXT>In a process for the manufacture of thermally highly loaded cooling elements,particularly of an acceleration grid having a large number of holes forneutral particle injection in fusion reactors, open cooling ducts areformed in a baseplate, in particular they were milled, and a cover plateis placed on top, after a layer of solder was placed between the two,and finally, the baseplate and cover plate are soldered together by heating.In order to ensure good soldering of the baseplate and cover plate withgreat leaktightness of the cooling ducts, spacer and a solder foil areprovided between the baseplate and the cover plate and the solderingis done with the cover plate at the bottom.</TEXT></DOC>